{
  "texts": [
    "There are distributed protocols in which all participants are known and which are designed for Byzantine fault tolerance [19,31,39,55].",
    "A notable example is IOTA [50], which has users create blocks containing their own transactions rather than relying on miners.",
    "These protocols use DAGs as a tool to reach consensus rather than to align participants' incentives, as we do.",
    "MAD-DAGMAD-DAG is a PoW blockchain protocol with a DAG structure.",
    "Each block contains a list of transactions, and one or more pointers to previous blocks, making it a DAG."
  ]
}